\pard\intbl \fs18 Standalone battle log viewer. Accepts a huntRef (e.g. 53935-762160), fetches from Firebase via server proxy, displays HP/MP bars (heroes from side "1", enemies from "-1"), and a scrollable turn-by-turn log. Auto-refreshes every 3s while live.\cell
\row
\pard\sb400\sa120\keepn\b\fs36\cf1 6. Summary\b0\fs22\cf0\par
\pard\li0\sb60\sa120 \fs22 The PVE Hunt Companion is a working, end-to-end real-time combat advisor. The Chrome Extension observes the DFK game UI through a layered parser and network interceptor stack, deduplicates events, and routes them to the Hedge Ledger backend over WebSocket \u8212? falling back to a persisted HTTP queue when the socket is unavailable. The backend stores every event, rebuilds the current BattleState, scores all legal actions using a weighted model, and pushes recommendations to the admin dashboard in real time.\par
\pard\li0\sb60\sa120 \fs22 The Firebase Battle Log panel provides an official view of the same battle sourced directly from DFK's Firestore database, serving as a ground-truth reference alongside the extension-parsed data. The two views together let an operator verify that the extension is capturing events correctly and that recommendations are landing on the right hero and enemy states.\par
\pard\li0\sb60\sa120 \fs22 The main open challenges are: reliable hero HP seeding before the first parser reading is stable; ensuring the in-memory companion session exists for the HTTP-only path when WS never connected; hunt ID detection robustness in the React SPA; and ongoing maintenance of the enemy catalog as new enemy types are added to the game.\par
\pard\li0\sb60\sa120 \fs22 The architecture is deliberately modular \u8212? the scoring engine, enemy catalog, master data, and feature extractor are all standalone server modules that can be iterated independently. The policy blender and Monte Carlo simulation modules are scaffolded for deeper lookahead capabilities when the real-time performance baseline is proven sufficient.\par

